contentrichtext.text: '''HRR''' may stand for: * [[The History of Rock and Roll]], a radio documentary produced by [[Bill Drake]] * [[Henley Royal Regatta]], a rowing event held in [[Henley-on-Thames]] annually * ''Heiliges Römisches Reich'', German name of the [[Holy Roman Empire]] * [[Heart rate#Heart rate reserve|Heart Rate Reserve]] * [[Historicorum Romanorum reliquiae]], a collection of ancient fragmentary Latin history-works * [[HRR 98.5FM]] * [[High Resolution Radar]] * [[Haploid-relative-risk]], a method for determining gene allele association to a disease * [[Hockey Related Revenue]], a term used in negotiations between the National Hockey League and the NHL Players Association * [[Hospital Referral Region]], a regional market area for tertiary medical care * [[Hirzebruch–Riemann–Roch theorem]] * [[Heat Release Rate]], the rate of heat released (e.g. in a combustion engine) {{disambig}}
